WEBVTT

00:00.220 --> 00:01.359
Here's what you missed on Glee:

00:01.359 --> 00:03.281
Kurt's still getting harassed and
doesn't know what to do about it.

00:03.282 --> 00:04.300
I am gonna kill you.

00:04.301 --> 00:06.140
Finn and Kurt got mad 
at each other, because Kurt had

00:06.141 --> 00:08.095
a crush on Finn, and then
Finn called him a nasty name,

00:08.096 --> 00:09.954
but it also wasn't cool that
Kurt couldn't take a hint,

00:09.955 --> 00:11.853
and their parents are dating,
so it's a little awkward.

00:11.854 --> 00:13.007
Sam and Quinn are sort of dating,

00:13.008 --> 00:14.209
and Sue sort of
dated Rod Remington.

00:14.210 --> 00:15.625
You sunk my battleship,

00:15.626 --> 00:17.527
Rod, and you sunk it hard.

00:17.528 --> 00:19.486
But then she caught him cheating,
so she's back on the market,

00:19.487 --> 00:21.278
and that's what you
missed on Glee.

00:29.965 --> 00:31.876
Oh. What's going on?

00:32.336 --> 00:33.928
Is this one of those
interventions, 'cause...?

00:33.929 --> 00:35.308
If it is, it's for the both of us.

00:35.309 --> 00:37.253
They bombarded me and forced
me to bring them to you.

00:37.254 --> 00:38.205
Okay, come on, tell 'em.

00:38.206 --> 00:38.994
- No, no, no, you.
- Come on.

00:38.995 --> 00:40.073
No. We said in the car.

00:40.074 --> 00:40.815
Come on, you, you.

00:40.816 --> 00:41.584
- Come on, you.
- Please!

00:41.585 --> 00:44.906
All right, so you know how I drive
Carole to work every Tuesday?

00:44.989 --> 00:47.277
Well, today I drove here,

00:47.278 --> 00:50.659
and we snuck into that classroom
where Kurt introduced us...

00:50.660 --> 00:53.450
very romantic of me,
I might add... And I...

00:53.451 --> 00:54.892
He proposed! He proposed!

00:54.893 --> 00:56.334
You stole the punch line!

00:56.588 --> 00:57.564
Come on!

00:57.565 --> 00:59.093
Wow. This just happened?

00:59.094 --> 01:00.420
Oh, Dad!

01:00.634 --> 01:02.539
Oh! We wanted the two of you
to be the first to know.

01:02.540 --> 01:04.031
Yeah, after the kids
in that homeroom.

01:04.032 --> 01:05.996
Come on, family hug, huh?

01:05.997 --> 01:07.060
Okay. Come on!

01:09.916 --> 01:11.677
I'm so excited and-and nervous!

01:11.678 --> 01:12.877
- Oh, don't be, don't be.
- Well, no. Okay.

01:12.878 --> 01:14.307
Oh, my God, this is
just what I needed.

01:14.308 --> 01:15.669
I will take care of it from here.

01:15.670 --> 01:18.626
I have a trunk full of wedding
magazines hidden under my bed.

01:18.627 --> 01:21.490
I'm thinking of a
russet and cognac theme.

01:21.491 --> 01:23.456
Those are colors, Finn.
Fall wedding colors.

01:23.457 --> 01:24.070
Autumnal.

01:24.071 --> 01:25.515
Nothing too extravagant,
Kurt, okay?

01:25.516 --> 01:26.761
We're gonna use whatever
savings we have.

01:26.762 --> 01:28.369
We are spending it
on the honeymoon.

01:28.370 --> 01:29.895
That's right.
We're going to Waikiki.

01:29.896 --> 01:30.770
We're gonna go to the hotel

01:30.771 --> 01:32.387
where they put up the
guest stars on Lost.

01:32.388 --> 01:34.292
Finn, you-you haven't
said anything.

01:34.293 --> 01:35.699
Uh, I'm...

01:35.700 --> 01:37.407
I guess I'm just kind of stunned.

01:37.517 --> 01:39.743
Hey, don't worry. I'm already
looking for a bigger house.

01:39.744 --> 01:42.016
One where everybody's gonna get
their own rooms. All right?

01:42.017 --> 01:44.488
Come on, honey. Be happy for me.

01:46.805 --> 01:47.974
I am, Mom.

01:47.975 --> 01:49.209
All right, now listen, Kurt,

01:49.210 --> 01:50.947
Mr. Wedding Planner, I want
you to take care of one thing.

01:50.948 --> 01:53.225
I don't care about the food
or the booze at this party,

01:53.226 --> 01:54.849
but I want one heck of a band.

01:55.005 --> 01:55.915
I've been eating right.

01:55.916 --> 01:57.148
I've been exercising.

01:57.928 --> 01:59.478
And I want to boogie with
Carole at this wedding.

02:00.705 --> 02:01.671
And I will boogie.

02:01.672 --> 02:03.284
All right. It's already
taken care of, Dad.

02:03.285 --> 02:05.691
I'm going to hire the New
Directions as your band.

02:05.692 --> 02:07.345
Right? It won't cost you a cent.

02:07.346 --> 02:08.663
They're cheap, they're available.

02:09.175 --> 02:10.424
Long story short...

02:11.030 --> 02:12.488
you're having a Glee wedding.

02:16.289 --> 02:18.787
Today is a red-letter day.

02:19.093 --> 02:22.621
The big day has finally
arrived for one Sue Sylvester.

02:22.622 --> 02:24.107
Becky, get in here!

02:24.108 --> 02:27.715
Get these invites down
to the post office, stat.

02:27.923 --> 02:29.108
Got it, Coach.

02:29.851 --> 02:34.407
And to think that this joyous
occasion began in horror.

02:34.408 --> 02:38.361
which is why I just prefer to
think of the homeless as outdoorsy.

02:38.362 --> 02:40.230
So shine on, urban campers!

02:40.231 --> 02:42.002
You smell like adventure!

02:42.003 --> 02:44.720
And that's how Sue sees it.

02:44.721 --> 02:47.236
Sue, you're the bee's knees.

02:47.237 --> 02:48.182
Before we break,

02:48.183 --> 02:49.697
I'd like to make an announcement.

02:49.698 --> 02:51.626
Rod and I are engaged.

02:52.556 --> 02:54.835
I popped the question
in my building's

02:54.836 --> 02:57.493
common-use hot tub. Booyah.

02:57.494 --> 02:58.639
Not to worry, ladies.

02:58.640 --> 03:00.118
It's an open marriage.

03:00.119 --> 03:01.305
We'll be right back.

03:01.377 --> 03:03.883
How dare you humiliate
me like that!

03:03.884 --> 03:05.394
People know you and I dated.

03:05.395 --> 03:08.531
Sue, you can't tame the tiger.

03:08.532 --> 03:10.260
You've read my tattoos.

03:10.261 --> 03:11.157
Face it, Sue.

03:11.158 --> 03:12.637
You're never going
to find someone,

03:12.638 --> 03:14.433
and you're going to die alone.

03:15.599 --> 03:18.927
So I decided to try online dating.

03:21.234 --> 03:24.244
And there was only one
match for Sue Sylvester.

03:26.292 --> 03:28.722
One Sue Sylvester.

03:30.416 --> 03:32.116
So thanks, eDesperate.

03:32.117 --> 03:33.873
I'm over the moon.

03:33.874 --> 03:36.220
Or maybe I'm a little
high off this adhesive,

03:36.221 --> 03:38.951
but I want to scream from
the highest mountain,

03:38.952 --> 03:42.440
"Sue Sylvester is
marrying herself."

03:46.227 --> 03:48.551
Hey, is that safe?

03:48.552 --> 03:50.080
With your shoulder
messed up and all?

03:50.081 --> 03:51.992
Doesn't feel messed up to me.
Now that I'm healthy,

03:51.993 --> 03:53.474
I'm going to be gunning
to get my job back.

03:53.698 --> 03:56.700
Well, Coach Beiste isn't going to
replace me while we're winning.

03:56.701 --> 03:58.066
You can't win every game.

03:58.067 --> 03:59.939
Look, I still want to
be friends. It's just,

03:59.940 --> 04:02.903
I'm kind of on the cusp of being one
of the most popular guys in school.

04:03.796 --> 04:05.065
Wow. I, uh...

04:05.206 --> 04:07.403
I didn't think you were the type
that cared about that stuff.

04:07.404 --> 04:09.311
Everyone does. Being on top

04:09.312 --> 04:10.764
means you don't have to
take crap from anybody.

04:10.765 --> 04:13.100
No teasing, no Slushee facials.

04:13.540 --> 04:15.668
Being quarterback isn't
going to put you on top,

04:16.601 --> 04:19.617
especially since you can't even
get Quinn to be your girlfriend.

04:19.618 --> 04:20.812
I'm working on that, too.

04:22.000 --> 04:28.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

04:30.403 --> 04:32.415
So, what do you want to
talk about in private?

04:32.416 --> 04:35.880
These galactic mobiles
aren't the stars of McKinley.

04:36.484 --> 04:37.504
We are.

04:37.868 --> 04:39.383
Or at least, I want us to be.

04:39.384 --> 04:40.445
Okay.

04:41.991 --> 04:43.311
I think I love you.

04:46.553 --> 04:49.424
Look, my shoulder's healed, I'm going
to be the quarterback again soon.

04:49.572 --> 04:51.253
And you're already
the head cheerleader.

04:53.299 --> 04:55.163
Oh, my God, are you proposing?

04:55.285 --> 04:57.470
We've known each other
for six weeks. Stand up.

04:57.471 --> 04:59.453
- You're freaking me out.
- I want to marry you...

04:59.780 --> 05:01.977
some day. Until then,

05:01.978 --> 05:03.801
will you accept this promise ring?

05:04.895 --> 05:06.570
What are you, six?

05:06.571 --> 05:08.043
If you accept,

05:08.983 --> 05:12.399
this ring will symbolize my
promise to you to be true,

05:12.400 --> 05:15.759
to never pressure you to
do anything more than kiss,

05:15.760 --> 05:16.855
to listen to your problems,

05:16.856 --> 05:19.412
to tell you when you
have food in your teeth

05:19.413 --> 05:21.715
or eye gunk, to come over to
your house whenever you need

05:21.716 --> 05:23.284
something super
heavy moved around.

05:23.742 --> 05:27.203
I promise to make you feel proud

05:27.204 --> 05:29.817
when you point down
the hall and say,

05:29.818 --> 05:31.531
"That dude's my boyfriend."

05:31.713 --> 05:34.265
And I promise to do
all of those things

05:34.293 --> 05:36.593
without ever trying to sound
like Matthew McConaughey.

05:41.973 --> 05:43.702
I really care about you, Quinn.

05:45.360 --> 05:46.810
And I want us to be together.

05:53.790 --> 05:54.915
Is that a no?

05:55.981 --> 05:57.257
It's a maybe.

06:09.558 --> 06:12.057
Hey, uh, so I've been
reviewing this itinerary,

06:12.058 --> 06:13.497
and I don't really get it.

06:13.498 --> 06:16.040
Are you sure we should release
300 live doves indoors?

06:16.041 --> 06:17.778
Won't that get kind of messy?

06:17.779 --> 06:19.681
That's why we feed
them glitter, Finn.

06:20.220 --> 06:23.457
Oh. Well, look,
I've been thinking about it.

06:23.458 --> 06:25.780
I really want to do something
special for the wedding, and

06:25.781 --> 06:27.022
I wanted to take this opportunity

06:27.023 --> 06:31.780
to sort of remind everyone that I'm,
you know, a leader.

06:32.132 --> 06:33.547
I have the perfect idea.

06:33.771 --> 06:35.255
After you walk your
mom down the aisle,

06:35.256 --> 06:36.567
and give her away to my dad...

06:36.568 --> 06:37.242
Incredibly creepy.

06:37.243 --> 06:38.733
and give your speech
to the newlyweds...

06:38.734 --> 06:40.294
which I will write,
although you are free

06:40.295 --> 06:41.642
to suggest overall themes...

06:41.643 --> 06:43.208
you and Carole will have a lovely

06:43.209 --> 06:44.696
mother-and-son dance
in front of everyone.

06:44.697 --> 06:45.992
Ah, that's a terrible idea.

06:45.993 --> 06:47.645
Everybody knows I'm
the worst dancer.

06:47.646 --> 06:48.725
Finn, trust me on this.

06:48.726 --> 06:50.677
I've been planning
weddings since I was two.

06:50.678 --> 06:52.435
My Power Rangers got
married and divorced

06:52.436 --> 06:54.277
in so many combinations,
they were like Fleetwood Mac.

06:54.278 --> 06:55.731
I guess if I could pull it off,

06:56.574 --> 06:58.698
it would make me seem
like a cool stud.

06:58.699 --> 06:59.836
Totally.

06:59.912 --> 07:01.780
Thanks. It's a plan.

07:11.201 --> 07:12.671
I don't want you near me.

07:24.678 --> 07:25.790
Can I have this?

07:28.292 --> 07:29.488
Thanks.

07:35.419 --> 07:36.351
Are you okay?

07:38.879 --> 07:39.739
No. No.

07:39.740 --> 07:41.822
Okay, let's go to the
principal, come on.

07:43.430 --> 07:45.096
Did he physically hurt you?

07:46.432 --> 07:47.014
No.

07:47.015 --> 07:48.667
You said he's shoved you
into the lockers before.

07:48.668 --> 07:50.269
Well, I can't expel
a kid for shoving.

07:50.270 --> 07:52.425
He'll just say, "I didn't mean
to shove that kid, I tripped!"

07:52.426 --> 07:53.543
Excuse works like a charm.

07:53.544 --> 07:54.501
I use it all the time.

07:54.502 --> 07:55.953
He didn't shove me this time.

07:55.954 --> 07:58.229
He just... terrified me.

07:58.230 --> 08:01.750
Lady, I can't suspend a
student because he scares you.

08:01.751 --> 08:04.690
High school is a dry run
for the rest of your life.

08:04.691 --> 08:07.030
It's rough. People can be mean.

08:07.031 --> 08:08.145
That's your advice?

08:08.372 --> 08:09.530
That's all you have to say?

08:09.531 --> 08:11.930
William, I was bullied
my entire life.

08:12.158 --> 08:14.295
I grew up with a
handicapable sister.

08:14.296 --> 08:17.040
I know very well how
cruel people can be.

08:17.041 --> 08:18.689
Was it difficult? Yes.

08:18.924 --> 08:20.329
Did it make me stronger?

08:21.139 --> 08:22.011
You bet it did.

08:22.012 --> 08:23.664
It's the fear that's the worst.

08:24.392 --> 08:26.986
I never know when it's coming,
I can't concentrate,

08:26.987 --> 08:28.799
I don't feel like I'm part
of this school at all.

08:28.800 --> 08:30.753
I feel like I'm in a horror
movie where this creature

08:30.754 --> 08:32.181
follows me around terrifying me,

08:32.182 --> 08:34.068
and there's nothing
that I can do about it?

08:34.070 --> 08:35.032
I mean, you...

08:35.416 --> 08:37.505
You don't know what's going
on in this kid's head.

08:37.506 --> 08:38.999
You don't know what
he's capable of.

08:42.053 --> 08:43.057
What does that mean?

08:43.192 --> 08:45.217
Nothing. Maybe I'm overreacting.

08:45.218 --> 08:48.959
Lady, this kid lays a finger on you,
you come straight to me,

08:48.960 --> 08:50.456
and I will expel him faster

08:50.457 --> 08:53.581
than a Thai take-out place can
read back your delivery order.

08:53.582 --> 08:54.735
Okay?

08:54.736 --> 08:55.733
But until that happens,

08:55.734 --> 08:58.151
and I'm genuinely
sorry to say this,

08:58.515 --> 09:01.360
there is nothing legally I
or the school board can do.

09:03.125 --> 09:03.641
Come on, Kurt.

09:03.642 --> 09:05.046
We're gonna be late for rehearsal.

09:09.890 --> 09:12.591
You know, when you call me lady...
That's bullying.

09:13.195 --> 09:14.151
And it's really hurtful.

09:14.152 --> 09:15.985
I'm sorry. I thought
that was your name.

09:15.986 --> 09:17.362
As an apology, I'll allow you

09:17.363 --> 09:19.142
to choose from the
following nicknames...

09:19.143 --> 09:22.756
Gelfling, Porcelain,
and Tickle-Me-Doughface.

09:24.214 --> 09:25.330
I guess I'll go with Porcelain.

09:25.331 --> 09:27.835
Damn. Totally wanted
Tickle-Me-Doughface.

09:29.514 --> 09:31.845
Ladies, the Kurt-Karofsky
bullying situation

09:31.846 --> 09:33.171
is getting way out of control.

09:33.172 --> 09:34.915
Kurt's miserable,
he's losing weight...

09:34.916 --> 09:36.127
and not in a good way.

09:36.128 --> 09:38.316
And he's barely even fighting
me for solos anymore.

09:38.317 --> 09:39.517
We've all been teased,
but something

09:39.518 --> 09:41.302
about what Karofsky's
doing is so much worse.

09:41.303 --> 09:43.236
We're all lucky enough to have
boyfriends on the football team.

09:43.237 --> 09:46.236
I say, we band together and demand
that they confront Karofsky.

09:46.237 --> 09:47.963
Okay, first off all,
I'm not dating Sam.

09:47.964 --> 09:49.063
And second of all,

09:49.064 --> 09:50.409
I think you personally just set

09:50.410 --> 09:52.013
the feminist movement
back 50 years.

09:52.014 --> 09:54.010
But guys like Karofsky
only respond to muscle.

09:54.011 --> 09:56.158
So we're going to fight
violence with violence? No!

09:56.159 --> 09:58.563
Look, I'm not saying
that they should hit him.

09:58.564 --> 10:00.458
What I'm saying is that
we need to defend Kurt,

10:00.459 --> 10:01.845
and there's strength in numbers.

10:01.846 --> 10:05.005
I'm confused. Are you and
Artie officially dating now?

10:05.147 --> 10:06.119
Deal with it.

10:07.462 --> 10:09.512
When you guys fooled around,
did he ever, like,

10:09.513 --> 10:10.608
just lie there?

10:10.830 --> 10:12.196
Why didn't you tell
me that we were having

10:12.197 --> 10:13.250
a Glee girls meeting?

10:13.251 --> 10:14.966
This is a meeting for Glee
girls with boyfriends.

10:14.967 --> 10:17.483
We're going to make them stop
Karofsky from bullying Kurt.

10:17.593 --> 10:20.264
Okay, I'm dating Puckerman.
You're getting naked with Puckerman.

10:20.265 --> 10:22.873
Besides, Puck can't mess with Karofsky;
He's on probation.

10:22.874 --> 10:24.919
If he gets in a fight with him,
he'll be sent back to juvee.

10:24.920 --> 10:27.224
Mm-hmm. Yeah,
so now if you'll excuse us.

10:28.487 --> 10:30.416
You're so on my list, dwarf.

10:31.606 --> 10:33.972
Look, if something
bad happens to Kurt,

10:33.973 --> 10:36.035
and we didn't do
anything to stop it,

10:36.281 --> 10:38.203
we'll never be able to
live with ourselves.

10:39.441 --> 10:40.621
I'm a little confused.

10:40.622 --> 10:43.353
I said not only am
I marrying myself,

10:43.354 --> 10:45.124
I will be officiating
the ceremony.

10:45.125 --> 10:46.090
I'm not, um...

10:46.091 --> 10:47.871
Marsha Dean, when I hired you

10:47.872 --> 10:50.102
and your crack team at
Marsha Dean Weddings,

10:50.103 --> 10:52.928
I did so because you
specialize in unique weddings.

10:52.929 --> 10:56.372
Well, that mostly means that
some of them take place outside.

10:56.373 --> 10:57.789
Marsha Dean, you are fired.

10:57.790 --> 10:58.972
You are out of your depth.

10:58.973 --> 11:01.449
And nothing is too
good for Sue Sylvester.

11:01.450 --> 11:03.354
Well, that's one
way to look at it.

11:03.524 --> 11:04.672
Hello.

11:05.306 --> 11:06.905
I'm Doris Sylvester.

11:06.906 --> 11:08.246
I'm this one's mother.

11:08.247 --> 11:11.400
Marsha, I'll bet people
say you look mannish.

11:11.401 --> 11:12.612
But you know something?

11:12.613 --> 11:16.075
I think it's perfectly all right
for a woman to be handsome.

11:19.190 --> 11:20.344
Takes all kinds.

11:20.868 --> 11:24.371
Susie, come give
your mother a hug.

11:25.364 --> 11:26.728
Please don't call me that.

11:26.865 --> 11:28.185
Come on, come on.

11:32.061 --> 11:34.276
Oh, you poked me in my sternum.

11:34.674 --> 11:37.565
I always forget that
you have this ribcage

11:37.566 --> 11:38.893
that's kind of weird...

11:38.894 --> 11:41.382
and adorable.
I think I'll sit down.

11:42.647 --> 11:44.571
Mom, what are you doing here?

11:44.572 --> 11:48.328
Good news, Suze.
We finally caught the last Nazi.

11:48.329 --> 11:50.719
For two and a half years,
we've been hot

11:50.720 --> 11:54.603
on the trail of Eva
Braun's great-nephew Chad.

11:54.604 --> 11:57.293
And you know what? He's been
under our noses this whole time.

11:57.294 --> 11:59.420
Working in Phoenix as a CPA.

12:00.807 --> 12:03.589
I felt bad taking him out.

12:03.817 --> 12:06.155
I mean, it's punishment
enough to live there.

12:06.403 --> 12:08.433
You ever been to Phoenix?
It's a hellhole.

12:08.434 --> 12:09.670
Mom, where have you been?

12:09.671 --> 12:11.468
I haven't seen you
or heard from you

12:11.469 --> 12:12.658
- in over three years.
- What do you mean?

12:12.659 --> 12:14.956
I-I wrote you all those postcards.

12:14.957 --> 12:17.270
I mean, granted, they were decoys.

12:17.271 --> 12:18.788
Have you been to see Jean yet?

12:18.789 --> 12:20.361
It's the top of my list.

12:21.373 --> 12:22.784
Look, I, uh...

12:23.129 --> 12:25.391
I know it's been a
long time, but...

12:25.994 --> 12:28.216
the work I was doing
was important.

12:28.426 --> 12:30.299
And I always wanted
to get back here

12:30.300 --> 12:33.326
and be a mother to
you girls again.

12:34.025 --> 12:35.725
And Susie, I have to ask you,

12:35.726 --> 12:38.366
what is it with this
ridiculous wedding?

12:38.367 --> 12:39.518
Have you given up on love?

12:39.519 --> 12:40.983
No, Mother. Quite the opposite.

